      "text": "I would treat this like I would run any opensource group.  Communication channels are king.  Have a kickoff summit week in person.  Then go back to \"offsite\" mode when you need to get work done for yourself.  Group chat-rooms facilitate knowledge dissemination.  Chat bots (I've had success with both IRC and skype group chats) can facilitate the communication in areas where people might be slightly lacking and provide an engaging experience in the group chat."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
